6:
I already told you! You don't NEED to
be creative! Leave that to more
experienced chefs!
15:
Nuh-uh! No ifs, ands, buts, or
coconuts! Stick to the recipe! And
what did the recipe say? Low flame,
Yuwel! LOW FLAME!
47:
No, no! It's great! I think it's a miracle
you got this far!
51:
It could use more seasoning, but it's
actually quite suitable.
57:
Now I am once again the only one
who can't cook...
61:
So, you're satisfied, right? No more
shoving zoni down our throats?
64:
Sorry... No more zoni, I promise.
But I'm not satisfied just yet.
66:
Alk, there is one more thing I'd like to
ask of you.
80: Phew... Alk, the rest is up to you.
87:
Mm... It's hard to describe, but the
soup you make tastes... better. More
comforting.
89:
I was wondering what you needed
all this foodstuff for... But I never
thought you planned on providing
dinner and a show for the little 'uns.
91:
I thought you were set on doing
everything yourself. What made you
change your mind?
94:
I wanted the children to have
something actually delicious. And to
that end, I was willing to let go of
some of my pride.
96:
But when the time comes for the
former Swallow Knights to reunite... I
think I'll make the whole feast myself.
98: Hah! That'll knock them for a loop.
100: Yuweeel! I finished! It was so good!
102:
What was the white stuff in the
soup? First it was like super stretchy,
and then it was chewy like gum? But
THEN, you could swallow it!
104:
It's called mochi. It's a food from a
distant land. The people there say
that if you eat enough, you'll grow
big and strong.
106:
Sooo... does that mean I can grow
up to be like you?
110:
Yuwel's a PRINCE! He's DIFFERENT
from us.
113:
N-no, that isn't true at all. First off, I'm
not a prince...
116:
But more importantly, nothing is
decided in this life.
118:
With enough hard work, there are
few paths that you cannot pave.
120:
To be honest, there was a time I
thought that cooking was a
hopeless task for me...
125:
Yes, but with aid from my friends, I
came through eventually.
127:
So remember, it's important to ask
for help where it's needed and give
help where it's wanted. That is the
true source of our strength.
133:
Wait... Does that mean I can be your
girlfriend?
148:
Nothing out of the ordinary.
Wherever he goes, Yuwel can hardly
keep the girls out of his hair.
153:
Hey, missie! I'd give up on that one if
I were you! The competition's fierce
and the prize not easily won.
160:
Huh? What competition? I wanna
know more!
